---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const siteName = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_SITE_NAME ?? "PricingNest";
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`COGS (Cost of Goods Sold) | ${siteName}`}
  description="COGS definition for SaaS, what typically goes in COGS, and how it connects to gross margin."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>COGS (Cost of Goods Sold)</h1>
    <p>COGS is the direct cost to deliver your product or service. For SaaS, COGS is usually a mix of infra + vendor costs.</p>
  </section>

  <div class="grid">
    <article class="card col8">
      <h2>Typical SaaS COGS components</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><strong>Infrastructure</strong>: compute, storage, bandwidth, managed services.</li>
        <li><strong>Third-party vendors</strong>: APIs, LLM providers, data providers, email/SMS, observability tools (if allocated per customer).</li>
        <li><strong>Support</strong>: if your accounting treats support as COGS; otherwise model it as an operating cost but still include it in pricing decisions.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">What usually is not COGS</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Sales and marketing spend (CAC), unless youâ€™re doing contribution margin modeling.</li>
        <li>Product engineering (R&amp;D).</li>
        <li>Corporate overhead.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Tools to use</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/glossary/gross-margin/">Gross margin</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/compute-cost-estimator/">Compute cost estimator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/storage-cost-calculator/">Storage cost calculator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/bandwidth-cost-calculator/">Bandwidth cost calculator</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <aside class="card col4">
      <h2>Related</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/glossary/unit-economics/">Unit economics</a></li>
        <li><a href="/glossary/cac/">CAC</a></li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

